(27, 0, 'Microsoft Surface Pro', 6, 'Nithin Balasubramanian', 'Microsoft Surface Pro is powered by a 1.3GHz quad-core NVIDIA Tegra 3 processor. ', '1597037762_a.jpg', '<p><strong>Microsoft Surface Details</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Microsoft Surface</strong>&nbsp;Pro is powered by a 1.3GHz quad-core NVIDIA Tegra 3 processor. It comes with 2GB of RAM. ... Connectivity options on the&nbsp;<strong>Microsoft Surface</strong>&nbsp;Pro include Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n and Wi-Fi Direct. Sensors on the tablet include accelerometer, ambient light sensor, gyroscope, and compass/ magnetometer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Microsoft Surface Pro tablet was launched in October 2012. The tablet comes with a 10.60-inch display with a resolution of 1366x768 pixels at a pixel density of 148 pixels per inch (ppi). Microsoft Surface Pro is powered by a 1.3GHz quad-core NVIDIA Tegra 3 processor. It comes with 2GB of RAM.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;As far as the cameras are concerned, the Microsoft Surface Pro on the rear packs 1.2-megapixel camera. It sports a 1.2-megapixel camera on the front for selfies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Microsoft Surface Pro based on Windows 8 and packs 32GB of inbuilt storage that can be expanded via microSD card (up to 64GB). The Microsoft Surface Pro measures 172.00 x 274.60 x 13.50mm (height x width x thickness) and weighs 680.40 grams. It was launched in Dark Titanium colour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Connectivity options on the Microsoft Surface Pro include Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n and Wi-Fi Direct. Sensors on the tablet include accelerometer, ambient light sensor, gyroscope, and compass/ magnetometer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn%3AANd9GcRJSuZ19TiJHH3e1YwlWEHFfNemiw9D9_db8w&amp;usqp=CAU\" style=\"height:100%; width:100%\" /></p>\r\n', '2020-08-10'),
